race.comment: STATION ONE (2) was back in the winners' list as public elect over 1900m at Traralgon a month ago. He is free running and will be suited around here. Jumps form a handy gate and his form is strong. RHINOCEROS (1) also races forward and will find this more suitable than Caulfield Heath last time. Country Cups are his go now, and he'll get every chance from an inside barrier. FATHER'S DAY (5) switched from a Sydney barn and didn't get warm at Ballarat first-up. Has the blinkers on again and certainly has the ability. Will push forward and has to be considered. FLYING BASIL (3) will be fitter and won't be too far away.
